# kerf.box — environment configuration
#
# Copy to `.env.local` (gitignored) and fill in what you need. The app
# degrades gracefully: with NONE of these set it still boots and serves
# demo content with no auth and an in-memory rate limiter. Add integrations
# as you turn features on. In production, set these in your host's env
# (e.g. Vercel project settings) — never commit real secrets.

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Inference (Anthropic)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Server-side key for live research + copy generation. Leave blank to serve
# demo content, OR let callers bring their own key per request (BYOK) via the
# X-Anthropic-Key header — that key is never stored or logged.
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
#
# Optional model overrides.
# KERFBOX_STRATEGY_MODEL=
# KERFBOX_COPY_MODEL=

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Auth (Clerk) — OPTIONAL
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Leave BOTH blank to run with no account system: pages are public, the API
# is reachable with BYOK only, and the rate limiter keys on IP. This is the
# zero-account, agent-first self-host mode.
#
# To enable hosted accounts, set both keys from your Clerk instance.
#   • pk_test_ / sk_test_  → Clerk DEVELOPMENT instance (clerk.accounts.dev).
#     Fine for local + previews. Rate-limited, shows a dev banner, and uses
#     Clerk's SHARED Google OAuth app.
#   • pk_live_ / sk_live_  → Clerk PRODUCTION instance. Requires a custom
#     domain with DNS records and your OWN Google OAuth credentials. This is
#     what a real launch should use.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=
# CLERK_SECRET_KEY=
#
# Sign-in/up routing is configured in code (app/layout.tsx ClerkProvider), so
# these are optional overrides only:
# NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_SIGN_IN_URL=/sign-in
# NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_SIGN_UP_URL=/sign-up

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Database (Supabase) — OPTIONAL (needed for saving kerfs / API keys)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR-PROJECT.supabase.co
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR-PROJECT.supabase.co
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=   # server-only; never expose to the client
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Billing (Stripe) — OPTIONAL (needed to charge for the Pro / in-house agent)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Leave ALL THREE blank and billing is OFF: the subscription gate fails open,
# so the in-house agent is unmetered. This is the correct self-host / OSS
# default — nobody is ever paywalled on their own deployment.
#
# To charge for Pro (flat $15/mo to run on our server key) on the hosted app:
#   1. STRIPE_SECRET_KEY  — sk_live_... (or sk_test_... while testing).
#   2. STRIPE_PRICE_ID    — price_... for a $15/mo recurring Price you create
#                           in the Stripe dashboard (Product → add price).
#   3. STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET — whsec_... from the webhook endpoint you register
#                           at https://<your-domain>/api/stripe/webhook for
#                           events: checkout.session.completed,
#                           customer.subscription.updated,
#                           customer.subscription.deleted.
# Billing turns on only when BOTH the secret key AND the price id are set.
# Full step-by-step setup lives in BILLING.md at the repo root.
# STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=
# STRIPE_PRICE_ID=
# STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Rate limiting (Upstash Redis or Vercel KV) — OPTIONAL
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Without these, limiting is in-memory per-instance. Set one pair for a
# durable, cross-instance limiter.
# UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL=
# UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN=
# KV_REST_API_URL=
# KV_REST_API_TOKEN=

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Site
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Canonical origin for metadata/sitemap/OG. Set to your deployment's URL.
# Defaults to https://kerfbox.vercel.app when unset.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=https://kerfbox.vercel.app
